<item>
            <title>[HBASE-8724] [0.94] ExportSnapshot should not use hbase.tmp.dir as a staging dir on hdfs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8724</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On 0.94, ExportSnapshot uses &quot;hbase.tmp.dir&quot; as the job&apos;s staging directory on hdfs. However, &quot;hbase.tmp.dir&quot; is by definition a local directory, thus should not be used as an hdfs directory for the job. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Trunk uses JobUtil.getStagingDir() which gets the staging dir from JobSubmissionFiles class in Hadoop, so trunk is fine. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ve discovered this since it fails the test on windows, but this is not windows-specific as per above (like specifying hbase.tmp.dir as /var/hbase/tmp/ etc)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
